body:
I have narrowed down the issue to a small testcase, which results in a Verilator internal error.
The file to be verilated: `vc.sv`:
```systemverilog
package pa_vc;
  localparam int param1 = 2;
  typedef enum int
  { ONE = 1
  , TWO = 2
  , THREE = 3
  , MAX
  } PARAMTYPE;
endpackage

module vc
#(paramOne = pa_vc::param1
, paramTwo = pa_vc::MAX
)(input  var [paramOne-1:0] a
, output var [paramOne-1:0] b
);
  assign b = a;
endmodule
```
The command used: `verilator --debug --gdbbt --lint-only vc.sv`
Output of the command: [output.log](https://github.com/verilator/verilator/files/8909807/output.log)

This was originally noticed with `v4.220-23` I believe, but was retested with a freshly compiled copy from git, which gives: `Verilator 4.223 devel rev v4.222-63-g0c2c0973`
The same results were noticed on both `CentOS Linux release 7.8.2003` and `Ubuntu 22.04 LTS under WSL2`
